[Name] cal3d
[Summary] A skeletal-based 3D character animation library written in C++.
[License] GNU Lesser General Public License (LGPL)
[Description] Cal3d is a skeletal-based 3D character animation library written in C++ in a platform-/graphic-API independent way. Originally designed to be used in a 3D client for Worldforge, it evolved into a stand-alone product which can be used in many different kinds of projects.
[Homepage] https://cal3d.sourceforge.net/
